cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel approach to perform static malware analysis using machine learning techniques. It falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with malware detection. The paper also uses natural language processing techniques, which makes it relevant to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of LSTM models for malware detection also makes it relevant to the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and neural networks (cs.NE).
